## Errors & Mistakes
- First duck-type draft used index signatures ([key: string]: unknown) and
  Record-typed config; real genai/ADK interfaces (Part, Content,
  GenerateContentConfig) have no index signatures, so WeaveAdkPlugin was not
  assignable to BasePlugin — exactly what users hit passing the plugin in
  RunnerConfig.plugins. Fixed by dropping index signatures, typing config as
  object, and listing common Part fields as unknown.
- /opt/homebrew/bin/node is a bun shim and npm is absent from PATH on this
  machine; use ~/.nvm/versions/node/v24.16.0/bin.

## Dead Ends
- OTel-based design (mirror the Python google_adk integration): rejected.
  ADK-JS emits spans via the GLOBAL OTel tracer; capturing them requires
  registering the global TracerProvider + ContextManager, which breaks any
  user OTel stack registered later (second registration is refused), and
  SDK 2.x removed addSpanProcessor so we cannot attach to a user provider.
  Python can patch ADK's tracing functions in-place; ESM immutable bindings
  + relative internal imports make that impossible in JS.
- Parenting @google/genai generateContent calls under ADK calls via OTel
  span-id correlation: without a registered ContextManager ADK context
  propagation is a no-op and NonRecording spans share the INVALID all-zero
  span id; module-global correlation breaks under ParallelAgent. Chose
  exclusion (PR 2/4) instead.

## Hints for Future Agents
- ADK 1.2.0 NEVER dispatches plugin beforeAgentCallback/afterAgentCallback
  (PluginManager.runBefore/AfterAgentCallback have zero call sites), hence
  lazy invoke_agent synthesis from callbackContext.agentName + the agent
  tree captured at beforeRun. Both agent callbacks ARE implemented so timing
  becomes exact if ADK wires them; afterAgentCallback deletes the map entry
  so LoopAgent re-runs would get fresh calls.
- PluginManager RETHROWS plugin callback errors into the user's run — every
  callback body goes through guard() (warnOnce + swallow). Never let a
  logging bug break the host app.
- afterModelCallback fires once per streamed response; partial=true chunks
  are skipped; the final aggregated response closes the call.
- afterToolCallback fires even after onToolErrorCallback handled the same
  call (result=null); endToolCall tolerates the missing map entry.
- CJS hook subPath is dist/cjs/index.js (@google/adk is type:module with a
  require condition). Patching Runner.prototype.runAsync/runEphemeral covers
  subclasses (InMemoryRunner); registration is idempotent via
  pluginManager.getPlugin('weave') and a globalSingleton plugin instance.
- If a run aborts mid-flight afterRun never fires; process.once('beforeExit')
  force-closes dangling calls with status 'interrupted'.
- Ordering requirement: import weave BEFORE @google/adk (CJS) or run with
  node --import=weave/instrument (ESM).

## Codebase Discoveries
- sdks/node has two ingestion paths: legacy calls API (default; used here)
  and OTel v2 /agents/otel/v1/traces via genai/provider.ts (piCodingAgent
  always; openai-agents only when WEAVE_USE_OTEL_V2=true).

## Open Questions
- When ADK starts dispatching plugin agent callbacks, consider whether the
